A shadowy figure hunched over a glowing vintage 1980s computer terminal in a dark room, their face illuminated only by the green phosphor glow of the CRT monitor displaying scrolling access logs and IP addresses. The scene is rendered in a moody noir style with dramatic venetian blind shadows casting stripes across the wall. A stern, watchful eye is reflected in the curved glass of the monitor screen. The atmosphere is tense and surveillance-heavy, with scattered punch cards and old network cables adding to the retro computing aesthetic. The color palette is dominated by deep blacks, muted browns, and that distinctive green terminal glow, evoking 1970s-80s computing paranoia. Vintage photography style with film grain and slight vignetting.
